setLists.title: Lying Bridge
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Lie in bed (or on the floor) facing the ceiling
  2. Put your hands below your buttocks
  3. Bend your knees so legs are at 45 degree angle (about 2 foot lengths from buttocks)
  4. Lift up your buttocks off the floor until your knees and shoulders create a straight line
  5. Hold for a quick pause (1-2 seconds) and bring your buttocks back to almost touching the floor
    • This counts as one rep.
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Lying Squeeze
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Lie in bed (or on the floor) facing the ceiling
  2. Put your hands below your buttocks
  3. Lift legs slightly off the floor, trying to keep legs straight
  4. Hold for 1 second
    • This counts as one rep.
  5. Go at your own pace
  6. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Soleus Push-up
setLists.caption: Ultra Low Impact Cardio
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Sit comfortably of the chair
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Keep your legs at 75-85 degrees (like the number seven: 7 ), with your feet just behind your knees
  4. Put weight on your toes (push into and slightly forward the floor) as you quickly raise your knees and heels off the floor
  5. Keep your toes planted on the floor
  6. Once you reach the top relax to let gravity instantly bring your heel back towards the floor
    • This counts a 1 repetition and should take about 1 second to complete
  7. If done correctly you could do this exercise for hours without fatigue
  8. Go at your own pace
  9. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Seated Chair March
setLists.caption: Low Impact Cardio
setLists.weights: You can use soup cans or weights if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Sit on the front half of the chair
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. March by lifting up your knees and moving your arms
  4. Go at your own pace
  5. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Seated Arm Raise
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.weights: You can use soup cans or weights if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Sit at the back of the chair
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Lift one arm directly above your head
  4. Return your arm to your side
  5. Repeat with the opposite side
    • this counts as 1 rep (repitition)
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Seated Leg Extension
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Sit at the front half of your chair
  2. Lean back to engage your core while holding yourself up with your hands
  3. From the knee lift one leg and then lower it more slowly
    • for a real challenge lift both legs at the same time
  4. Repeat with the opposite side
    • this counts as 1 rep (repitition)
  5. Go at your own pace
  6. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Seated No Rope Jump Rope
setLists.caption: Low Impact Cardio
setLists.weights: You can use soup cans or weights if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Sit on the front half of your chair
  2. Lean back slightly to engage your core
  3. Either choose to "bounce on the spot," or to do a calf raise
  4. At the same time rotate your arms in circles
    • 1 full arm rotation and raise up, or bounce counts as 1 rep
    • for a real challenge hold some food cans in each hand
  5. Go at your own pace
  6. [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Seated Row & Calf Raise
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.weights: You can use soup cans or weights if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Sit at the front of the chair
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Pretend strings are attached from your arms to your knees
  4. Lift your arms (like rowing) and raise on to the balls of your feet
    • try to pinch your shoulder blades at the top for better results
  5. Return your arms to your side while you lower your feet back to the floor
    • this counts as 1 rep (repitition)
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra rep, go for it!

setLists.title: Seated Chair Jog
setLists.caption: Low Impact Cardio
setLists.weights: You can use soup cans or weights if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Sit on the front half of the chair
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Use your arms and legs to run on the spot
    • One rep is when the same foot lands the second time, or around 1 second
  4. Go at your own pace
  5. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Single Leg Deadlift
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.weights: You can hold soup cans or weights in one hand if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand up and grasp on to the top of a chair
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Bend at the hips towards the floor, raise one leg behind you, and the opposite arm in front of you
  4. Now return to standing position and lower your arm and leg
  5. This counts a 1 repetition
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Holding Chair Squat
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand up and grasp on to the back of a chair
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Bend at the hips towards the floor, try to keep your feet flat on the floor and flex all your muscles
  4. Now return back to the starting position
  5. This counts a 1 repetition
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Wall Push-ups
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand up close to a wall (about two foot lengths back, the further you go the harder it is)
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can with legs shoulder width apart
  3. Place hands on wall and lower yourself towards the wall
  4. Now return back to the starting position by pressing up (if it's too difficult then walk closer to the wall to avoid injury)
  5. This counts a 1 repetition
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Marching on the Spot
setLists.caption: Low Impact Cardio
setLists.weights: You can use soup cans or weights if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand up and march on the spot
    2. <>Remember to sway your arms as you march
  2. Do left-right, or right-left if you prefer and this counts as one repetition
  3. Go at your own pace
  4. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Heel Lifts
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.weights: You can use soup cans or weights if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand up and grasp on to the back of a chair
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Raise both of your heels off the floor as high as you can go
  4. Now return back to the starting position
  5. This counts a 1 repetition
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Walking Jacks
setLists.caption: Low Impact Cardio
setLists.weights: You can use soup cans or weights if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand up with legs together
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Step out with one leg to one side and raise the same side arm above your head
  4. Now return back to the starting position
  5. Do the same on the other side and return to the start position
  6. This counts a 1 repetition
  7. Go at your own pace
  8. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Deadlift to Upright Row
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.weights: You can use soup cans or weights if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand up with legs shoulder width apart
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Start with arms relaxed in front of you
  4. Keep hands/fists together and slide them down as low as you can
  5. Now slide hands back up all the way to your chest
  6. This counts a 1 repetition
  7. Go at your own pace
  8. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Bent Over Rear Fly
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.weights: You can use soup cans or weights if you want to up the difficulty level
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand up with legs shoulder width apart
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can while bending at the hips
  3. Start with arms relaxed in front of you
  4. Put your hand together then left them out to the sides and squeeze shoulders and back when you reach the top
  5. Lower arms back down to relaxed in front of you
  6. This counts a 1 repetition
  7. Go at your own pace
  8. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Kneeling Push Up
setLists.caption: Medium Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Kneel on floor
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can with legs together, or crossed at the ankles
  3. Place hands on the floor and lower yourself towards the ground
  4. Now return back to the starting position by pressing up, try to keep your elbows close to your body and not like chicken wings
  5. This counts a 1 repetition
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Regular Push Up
setLists.caption: Regular Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Lie on floor keeping your back as straight as you can with legs together
  2. Place hands on the floor at chest height
  3. Raise your self up off the ground keeping your back as straight as possible
  4. Now return back to the starting position lowering yourself, try to keep your elbows close to your body and not like chicken wings
  5. This counts a 1 repetition
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Lying Down Squats
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Lye on floor
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Bend at the hips keeping the knees also bent, try to keep your back flat on the floor and flex all your muscles
  4. Straighten out your legs bringing them close to the floor
  5. Now bring your knees back up to the starting position
    6. This counts a 1 repetition
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Door Frame Squat
setLists.caption: Medium Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand up and grasp on to a door frame, about 1 step away from the frame
  2. Keep your back as straight as you can
  3. Bend at the hips towards the floor, try to keep your feet flat on the floor and flex all your muscles
  4. Now return back to the starting position
    5. This counts a 1 repetition
  5. Go at your own pace
  6. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Full Squat
setLists.caption: Normal Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand up keep your back as straight as you can
  2. Bend at the hips towards the floor, try to keep your feet flat on the floor and flex all your muscles
  3. Now return back to the starting position
  4. This counts a 1 repetition
  5. Go at your own pace
  6. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Back Widow (Elbow Press)
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Lie on your back with your knees bent
  2. Use your elbows to raise then lower yourself off the floor/bed
  3. Now return back to the starting position
  4. This counts a 1 repetition
  5. Go at your own pace
  6. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Leg Raise
setLists.caption: Low Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Lie in bed (or on the floor) facing the ceiling with legs straight an together
  2. Put your hands below your buttocks or at your sides, whatever is more comfortable
  3. Lift legs off the floor, trying to keep legs straight, while bringing legs to waist height.
  4. Keeping legs straight bring back to starting position
  5. Hold for 1 second
    • This counts as one rep.
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Side Bends
setLists.caption: Medium Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Stand with feet should width a part with hands on hips
  2. Raise one are in a straight line above your head
  3. Lower the arm back to the starting position
  4. This counts as one rep.
  5. Repeat on the other side
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Towel Pull Up Row
setLists.caption: Medium Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Lie in bed (or on the floor) facing the ceiling with legs straight an together
  2. Put your hands below your buttocks or at your sides, whatever is more comfortable
  3. Lift legs off the floor, trying to keep legs straight, while bringing legs to waist height.
  4. Keeping legs straight bring back to starting position
  5. Hold for 1 second
    • This counts as one rep.
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!

setLists.title: Half Cobra Push Up
setLists.caption: Medium Impact Resistance
setLists.body:
How to do it:
  1. Lie on floor
  2. Keep your legs together, or crossed at the ankles
  3. Place hands on the floor at chest height and raise yourself towards the ceiling while arching your back when you reach the top
  4. Lower youself back down
  5. This counts a 1 repetition
  6. Go at your own pace
  7. If you feel you can do [xtra-reps] extra reps, go for it!
